'''Clan Baird Society Worldwide'''<ref>{{cite web|title=Clan Baird|url=http://www.electricscotland.com/webclans/atoc/baird.html|website=Electric Scotland|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> is the oldest and largest modern Clan Baird group.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Council of Scottish Clans and Associations|title=Clan Registry|url=https://www.cosca.scot/find-your-clan-2/clan-registry/|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref>  It was established (1963) by Byron Owsley Baird and his wife Frances, in Florida, Unites States, and is a worldwide organization with members in [[Australia]], [[Scotland]], [[England]], [[New Zealand]], [[Canada]], [[Spain]], and the [[United States|U.S.]].  The Society is governed by a Board of Directors, Chieftains, and Honorary Chieftains,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Clan Baird Society|title=About Us|url=https://www.clanbairdsociety.com/the-organization|website=Clan Baird Society Worldwide|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> since Clan Baird is [[armigerous]].
The main objective of the group is to bring together [[List of Scottish clans|Bairds]] of the world, especially those who were a part of the diaspora after each [[Jacobite Rebellion|Scottish Rebellion]] and the [[Highland Clearances]], with those who remained in Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Baird|first1=Byron Owsley|title=Clan Baird Society Worldwide Past Presidents|url=https://www.clanbairdsociety.com/past-presidents-conveners|website=Clan Baird Society Worldwide|publisher=Heather Snyder|accessdate=7 April 2018}}</ref>

The Society holds biennial meetings in Scotland and the United States, the next cycle will be in 2019.  The 2017 meetings were held in [[Aboyne]], [[Aberdeenshire]], [[Scotland]] at the Boat Inn, and at the [[Grandfather Mountain Highland Games]], in [[Linville, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gryphon Summer 2017|first1=Clan Baird Society|title=Presidents Report|url=https://docs.wixstatic.com/ugd/14a474_42baa17eccf54074b696d89ce08b05dd.pdf|website=Clan Baird Society Worldwide|publisher=Debra Baird|accessdate=7 April 2018}}</ref>

Baird Archaeological and Historical Initiative (BAHI)<ref>{{cite web|last1=BAHI|title=Baird Archeological and Historical Initiative|url=https://www.clanbairdsociety.com/baird-archeaological-initiative|website=Clan Baird Society Worldwide|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref> is one of the most important aspects of the Society.  The BAHI sponsors projects in history and antiquities each year.  In 2017, the sponsored project was St. [[Drostan]]'s Pilgrimage Walk,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cook|first1=Gordon|title=St. Drostan the Focus of Hands-On Research|publisher=Fraserburgh Herald, Fraserburgh, Peterhead, Scotland|date=7 September 2017}}</ref> [[New Aberdour]], [[Aberdeenshire]], [[Scotland]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Roman Catholic Diocese of Aberdeen|first1=RCDA|title=Clan Baird Society Sponsors Local Pilgrimage|url=http://www.rcda.scot/archives/9822|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Roman Catholic Diocese of Aberdeen}}</ref>

